A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Fisheries – Striped Bass or Rockfish – Juvenile Survey
3 FOR the purpose of expanding the scope of the annual young–of–the–year juvenile survey
4 of striped bass or rockfish by requiring the Department of Natural Resources to
5 conduct the survey at sampling sites in the central region of the Maryland waters of
6 the Chesapeake Bay in addition to sampling sites in the northern and southern
7 regions of the Maryland waters of the Chesapeake Bay; establishing certain
8 requirements for the central region sampling sites; and generally relating to striped
9 bass or rockfish.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
11 Article – Natural Resources
12 Section 4–746
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Natural Resources
18 4–746.
19 (A) (1) The Department shall conduct annually a scientific survey to determine
20 the relative abundance of striped bass or rockfish of approximately 18 inches in length that
21 are in the Chesapeake Bay and its tributaries.
22 (2) The survey shall be conducted in areas that are used by the Department
23 to determine its young–of–the–year index of striped bass or rockfish.
