2 HOUSE BILL 889
1 (B) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
2 (1) CONDUCT THE ANNUAL YOUNG–OF–THE–YEAR JUVENILE SURVEY
3 OF STRIPED BASS OR ROCKFISH AT BETWEEN 12 AND 20, INCLUSIVE, SAMPLING
4 SITES LOCATED IN THE CENTRAL REGION OF THE MARYLAND WATERS OF THE
5 CHESAPEAKE BAY IN ADDITION TO SAMPLING SITES IN THE NORTHERN AND
6 SOUTHERN REGIONS OF THE CHESAPEAKE BAY; AND
7 (2) LOCATE THE CENTRAL REGION SAMPLING SITES IN ANY OF THE
8 FOLLOWING WATERS OF THE STATE:
9 (I) THE MAGOTHY RIVER;
10 (II) THE SEVERN RIVER;
11 (III) THE CHESTER RIVER;
12 (IV) THE SOUTH RIVER;
13 (V) THE WEST RIVER;
14 (VI) EASTERN BAY; OR
15 (VII) THE MILES RIVER.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
17 1, 2025.

